Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on understanding the trajectory of a viral meme in a social network and proposes algorithms to determine the path from a periphery shell to the core of the network. This falls under the scope of social and information networks.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes shell-based hill climbing algorithms to determine the path of a viral meme in a social network. This involves software engineering techniques and algorithms.
3. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with understanding the virality of a meme in a social network and proposes algorithms to determine its trajectory. This falls under the scope of computational social science.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes algorithms to determine the trajectory of a viral meme in a social network. This involves data structures and algorithms.
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper deals with understanding the virality of a meme in a social network and its impact on society. This falls under the scope of computers and society.
